<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-06-10T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-06-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="577" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853.51/363: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-10T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 10,
                                        1926—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>18. Your despatch No. 1470 May 17.<note n="20" xml:id="d577fn20">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <list>
                            <label>(1)</label>
                            <item>Has the requisite action been taken by the Portuguese authorities?
                                If not, you should remind them courteously of paragraphs 2 and 3 of
                                the Department’s No. 13, May 13, 7 p.m.</item>
                            <label>(2)</label>
                            <item>American holdings are unofficially estimated at 12,000 pounds
                                sterling but the number of American bond-holders is not known to the
                                Department.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>